 of motorcycle control and an accident."}]},{"node":"text","body":"\r\n\r\n\r\n"}],"severity":"warning","type":"general"},{"node":"safety","body":[{"node":"text","body":"\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n"},{"node":"consequence","body":[{"node":"text","body":"Ensure the preload assembly is fitted to the left hand fork leg. The preload assembly is identified by its shorter preload rod guide case. The top cap has a single preload adjuster."}]},{"node":"text","body":"\r\n"},{"node":"consequence","body":[{"node":"text","body":"Ensure the damper assembly is fitted to the right hand fork leg. The damper assembly is identified by its longer damper rod guide case. The top cap has two damping adjusters labelled TEN and COM."}]},{"node":"text","body":"\r\n"},{"node":"consequence","body":[{"node":"text","body":"The method for installing the preload or damping assembly and setting the oil level is the same for both forks. However, a different volume of oil will be required for each fork to achieve the oil level settings detailed above."}]},{"node":"text","body":"\r\n"},{"node":"consequence","body":[{"node":"text","body":"When fitting the fork top cap and fork preload/damping assembly, care must be taken not to damage the top ring of the assembly."}]},{"node":"text","body":"\r\n\r\n\r\n"}],"severity":"note","type":"notice"},{"node":"text","body":"\r\n"},{"node":"image-container","body":[{"node":"img","body":[],"href":"1697475211__Web.svg","id":"1697475211","name":"Fork preload and damping assemblies, L0323","type":"svg"},{"node":"text","body":"\r\n"},{"node":"table-container","body":[{"node":"table","body":[{"node":"tbody","body":[{"node":"text","body":"\r\n"},{"node":"tr","body":[{"node":"text","body":"\r\n"},{"node":"td","body":[{"node":"ol","body":[{"node":"li","body":[{"node":"p","body":[{"node":"text","body":"Preload assembly (left fork leg)"}],"type":"p_table_l"}]},{"node":"text","body":"\r\n"},{"node":"li","body":[{"node":"p","body":[{"node":"text","body":"Preload rod guide case"}],"type":